      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 869: The race detection relies on `time_t` equality, but `removed` has second-level granularity. If the user removes the conversation again within the same second while the re-invite clone is pending, `conv-\u003einfo.removed` can still equal `conv-\u003ereinviteRemoved`, causing the tombstone to be cleared and the conversation resurrected despite the newer local removal. Use a monotonic/local generation marker, clear `reinviteRemoved` in the removal path, or compare a value guaranteed to change on every removal rather than `time_t` alone.\n```suggestion\nif (conv-\u003ereinviteRemoved \u0026\u0026 conv-\u003ereinviteRemoved \u003d\u003d conv-\u003einfo.removed \u0026\u0026 !conv-\u003eremovalChangedDuringClone) {\n```\nThe exact fix should use the existing removal path to invalidate the pending re-invite marker whenever a local removal happens.",
